title: For Sale:  NEW Gen3 Glock 26 - USA MADE!!!!
postcontent: I have for sale a USA made Glock 26 that is brand new! Never even loaded. Comes in factory case with two 10 round mags and all papers. Glock has said that the USA made Glocks (17, 26 and 27) are made for export only to countries that dont have a trade agreement with Austria and these models are NOT to be sold in the USA. Glock has also changed the finish on these slides, they are not Tenifer. They are Melanite QPQ as Tenifer uses a cyanide base in the manufacturing process and is outlawed by the EPA. Therefore the slide finish is more of a dark matte grey than the standard "shiney" finish. Also, the chambering is on the top if the barrel, not on the ejection port side. The ejector has also been improved and tuned on these models. I am not going to list a price but instead will listen to all offers and the first offer I like will get it. I prefer a straight cash deal on this, but would consider a new/like new standard Glock 26 and some cash.  Please call/text me at REDACTED with any questions/offers. Thanks.

Back in the heyday of the TV Western, Steve McQueen, the star of "Wanted: Dead or Alive," rode across black-and-white screens toting a sidearm like nothing any lawman or outlaw had carried before. The large loop lever, coupled with the legendary crisp Henry action, makes it easy for you to enjoy those rapid-fire repeating shots Steve McQueen used to take down the bad guys.

Each is equipped with a saddle ring.

title: For Sale:  ( ͡° ͜ʖ ͡°)Stoeger 12 Ga. Coach Gun Nickel
postcontent:
Stoeger Nickel side by side Coach gun in 12 ga, $400  

Great for Cowboy action shooting or general home defense. Short and manuverable. Black Maple stock. Beautiful condition

Sorry, I don't have the original box and papers. Gun is in good fireable shape. It has been in the safe for many years only to be pulled and cleaned and inspected. Look at my other ads also. I will be selling the bulk of my collection over the next month or so to fund a large project. I will have some things for sale that will interest all different collectors and shooters.

Sales Order: 

If the ad is up and I do not list it as "sale pending" then it is still for sale. Do not message me with "do you still have it" or "is it still available". I will assume you are a spam bot trying to get my email address and I will ignore you. "I am interested" is a close second that is being used also. I myself answer an ad with where I am located and when I would be available. That always gets a persons attention. I try to sell to the first person who contacts me first. After that I contact the second response and so on. This had always worked for me in the past, but as time changed and more people flaked on me or wanted me to wait beyond an agreed upon time/day, I have changed my method to a "first with the cash gets the prize". As in everything communication is king, I can't read your mind. I am not interested in Shipping a gun anywhere but ike all things, If I get enough ridiculous offers and somebody just has to have this because it reminds them of the one dear old dad used to have and has more dollars than the local's sense, I will ship to your local FFL if he will accept a direct ship gun from a private owner. Postal Money order to be cleared first. I will not sell to a low baller, I will sell through afore mentioned Auction site or just keep the item.

Disclaimers and Information:

I am not a gun shop, there is no sales tax or background fees. I do not take credit cards. I also will not accept a cashier's check, personal check, money order or anything other than CASH. If you email me a low-ball offer and say that you will pay in CASH, like it is something special and I am selling a used car, I will assume you are a litttle retarded and shouldn't own a gun to begin with. Contact me and I will email the best pictures I can manage. No, I am not a professional photographer. I do not look at my phone all day hoping I have email. I check it when I get home from work and occasionally on the week ends. Please don't get discouraged and think I am ignoring you if I don't return an email in 5 minutes. I am not willing to drive across the state to meet you so that you can inspect the gun and make me an offer. Driving halfway across town is a different matter all together, but I hope you will have made your offer ahead of time. If not, I may take my toys and go home. Yes, I know what the asking price on Gunbroker is, I also know what they sell for along with shipping and transfer fee and credit card fee. I do not dignify ridiculous offers with a reasonable response, they will get a ridiculous response, if any response at all. I do not NEED to sell anything, I would just LIKE to. Reasonable offers are considered, not necessarily accepted, but considered. Please do not drag the moral character of my relatives into any disagreement, I can't help it, they are like that. Mom in particular. All firearms should be considered loaded at all times, they may not be, but it is safer to consider them that way. Spammers and scammers beware, I have a loaded LOIC (low orbit ion cannon) and I know how to use it. 

P.S. 

I am sorry this is sooo long but every day somebody fails to see reason and acts outside the bounds of my endurance. Check back often as the list continues to grow, ha.
